---
import CaseStudy from '../../layouts/CaseStudy.astro';
---
<CaseStudy slug="scandalous">
  <Fragment slot="meta">
    <div class="cs-meta-card">
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Client</div><div class="cs-meta-value">Scandalous Chocolates</div></div>
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Duration</div><div class="cs-meta-value">2017–Present</div></div>
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Role</div><div class="cs-meta-value">Brand &amp; GTM Lead via THIS</div></div>
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Industry</div><div class="cs-meta-value">Regulated Cannabis / Consumer CPG</div></div>
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Markets</div><div class="cs-meta-value">WA · OR · CA · IL · NY</div></div>
    </div>
  </Fragment>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="stat-strip">
      <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-num">$500K+</div><div class="stat-label">Raised through brand system</div></div>
      <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-num">13+</div><div class="stat-label">SKUs designed &amp; deployed</div></div>
      <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-num">5</div><div class="stat-label">State markets launched</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">Context · Action · Result · Ongoing</div>
    <div class="car-grid">
      <div class="car-sidebar">
        <div class="car-step active" onclick="switchCar(this,'car-sc-1')"><div class="car-step-label">01 · Context</div><div class="car-step-title">The situation</div></div>
        <div class="car-step" onclick="switchCar(this,'car-sc-2')"><div class="car-step-label">02 · Action</div><div class="car-step-title">What I did</div></div>
        <div class="car-step" onclick="switchCar(this,'car-sc-3')"><div class="car-step-label">03 · Result</div><div class="car-step-title">What it produced</div></div>
        <div class="car-step" onclick="switchCar(this,'car-sc-4')"><div class="car-step-label">04 · Ongoing</div><div class="car-step-title">Where it stands now</div></div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div id="car-sc-1" class="car-content">
          <div class="car-content-label">01 · Context</div>
          <div class="car-content-title">No brand. No packaging. No infrastructure.</div>
          <div class="car-content-body">Scandalous had a strong product: premium cannabis-infused chocolate. What it did not have was the system required to become a scalable regulated CPG brand.<br /><br />There was no visual identity, no packaging architecture, no investor narrative, no compliance framework, and no production pipeline. Every state expansion introduced a new layer of complexity. Washington, Oregon, California, Illinois, and New York each had their own labeling laws, warning requirements, child-resistant standards, THC content display rules, and compliance checkpoints.<br /><br />The challenge was not just building a brand. It was building one that could survive regulatory review in five different states while maintaining visual coherence, shelf presence, and premium positioning against established competitors like Grön and Kiva.</div>
        </div>
        <div id="car-sc-2" class="car-content" style="display:none">
          <div class="car-content-label">02 · Action</div>
          <div class="car-content-title">Full-cycle product commercialization across every touchpoint.</div>
          <div class="car-content-body">I built the entire brand system from scratch: identity, typography, color system, voice, and the signature lip motif that became the brand's core visual asset.<br /><br />That motif carried through every application, from the logo mark to the custom chocolate molds I developed with Tomric Systems, where each piece is embossed with the lips icon.<br /><br />I managed packaging production end-to-end with AEG Global, including dielines, substrate specifications, metallized polyester, soft touch laminates, PMS 440 C color callouts, and print approvals. I am credited as the artwork designer on the production files, and every SKU went through my hands from concept through signed master proof.<br /><br />I also navigated state-specific compliance for each market. That meant rebuilding regulatory panels, warning language, THC display hierarchy, and child-resistant packaging requirements for every new state entry. Five states, five regulatory environments, one brand system that stayed coherent across all of them.<br /><br />The product system expanded across multiple formats: single-serve pouches (10–20mg), 100mg breakable bars (10-piece format using custom Tomric mold), and the Smile format (two 50mg pieces in a new pouch architecture). Each format required its own packaging architecture, mold tooling, compliance review, and market positioning.<br /><br />Beyond packaging, I built the commercial layer around the brand: investor decks, pitch materials, sell sheets, dispensary-ready assets, and three generations of the website on Wix.</div>
        </div>
        <div id="car-sc-3" class="car-content" style="display:none">
          <div class="car-content-label">03 · Result</div>
          <div class="car-content-title">A real brand with real distribution.</div>
          <div class="car-content-body">Scandalous operates in five regulated state markets with 13+ SKUs deployed across multiple product formats.<br /><br />In New York alone, the brand is in 39 dispensaries with 14.6% weighted distribution. The most recent reporting period showed $10,700 in estimated sales, with steady-state revenue around $7,000/month on the 20mg product. The product is ranked #17 in New York cannabis chocolate by total sales volume, with 35.5% period-over-period growth.<br /><br />The investor-facing brand system I built helped raise $500K+ in funding. The packaging, mold designs, website, and brand assets I created are the ones still active in market today.<br /><br />The engagement has lasted nearly nine years, surviving product pivots, state expansions, format changes, ownership evolution, and shifting market conditions. Scandalous is the longest-running client relationship of my career.</div>
        </div>
        <div id="car-sc-4" class="car-content" style="display:none">
          <div class="car-content-label">04 · Ongoing</div>
          <div class="car-content-title">Active line extension and new market entry.</div>
          <div class="car-content-body">Current work includes the development of the 100mg bar line for New York, a 10-piece breakable bar format in dark chocolate, sea salt, and toffee. The line targets the higher-dose chocolate segment where Grön currently dominates.<br /><br />Five packaging concepts developed against competitive sales data, each balancing shelf differentiation, compliance clarity, and brand consistency.<br /><br />The 2026 roadmap includes the Smile format for Chicago, featuring two 50mg pieces in a new pouch architecture, plus additional flavor extensions across both New York and Chicago.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">Website — scandalouschocolates.com</div>
    <div class="browser-mockup" data-browser>
      <div class="browser-toolbar">
        <div class="browser-dots">
          <span class="browser-dot red" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <span class="browser-dot yellow" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <span class="browser-dot green" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="browser-url" data-browser-url>scandalouschocolates.com</div>
        <a class="browser-visit" href="https://www.scandalouschocolates.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Visit live site ↗</a>
      </div>
      <div class="browser-tabs" role="tablist">
        <button type="button" class="browser-tab active" data-tab="home" data-url="scandalouschocolates.com" role="tab" aria-selected="true">Home</button>
        <button type="button" class="browser-tab" data-tab="products" data-url="scandalouschocolates.com/products" role="tab" aria-selected="false">Products</button>
        <button type="button" class="browser-tab" data-tab="story" data-url="scandalouschocolates.com/our-story" role="tab" aria-selected="false">Our Story</button>
        <button type="button" class="browser-tab" data-tab="locations" data-url="scandalouschocolates.com/find-us" role="tab" aria-selected="false">Find Us</button>
        <button type="button" class="browser-tab" data-tab="contact" data-url="scandalouschocolates.com/contact" role="tab" aria-selected="false">Contact</button>
      </div>
      <div class="browser-viewport">
        <img class="browser-shot active" data-tab="home" src="/Personal/Images/Scandalous/scandalous-web-home.jpg" alt="Scandalous Chocolates homepage" loading="lazy" />
        <img class="browser-shot" data-tab="products" src="/Personal/Images/Scandalous/scandalous-web-products.jpg" alt="Scandalous products page" loading="lazy" />
        <img class="browser-shot" data-tab="story" src="/Personal/Images/Scandalous/scandalous-web-story.jpg" alt="Scandalous our story page" loading="lazy" />
        <img class="browser-shot" data-tab="locations" src="/Personal/Images/Scandalous/scandalous-web-locations.jpg" alt="Scandalous find us page" loading="lazy" />
        <img class="browser-shot" data-tab="contact" src="/Personal/Images/Scandalous/scandalous-web-contact.jpg" alt="Scandalous contact page" loading="lazy" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">Key Insight</div>
    <div class="foundation-card">
      <div class="foundation-section-title">This is product commercialization, not graphic design.</div>
      <div class="foundation-desc">The value was not the packaging alone. The value was the system that made the packaging shippable, compliant, scalable, and commercially useful across five regulatory environments.</div>
      <div class="foundation-desc">Mold engineering, substrate specs, compliance navigation, THC hierarchy, competitive positioning, investor storytelling, and dispensary-facing sales materials were all part of the same pipeline.</div>
      <div class="foundation-desc">That is the same skill set I applied at Infinity, where I supported $10M+ in licensing contracts and 50+ SKUs, and at Kraft Heinz, where I produced 800+ assets across approximately 30 brands.</div>
      <div class="foundation-desc" style="margin-bottom:0">The through-line is simple: building the systems that help products reach shelves.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</CaseStudy>

<style>
  .browser-mockup{border:1px solid var(--border2);border-radius:var(--r-lg);overflow:hidden;background:var(--bg);box-shadow:0 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.04),0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,.03)}
  .browser-toolbar{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:14px;padding:10px 14px;background:var(--bg2);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border)}
  .browser-dots{display:flex;gap:6px;flex-shrink:0}
  .browser-dot{width:11px;height:11px;border-radius:50%;display:inline-block}
  .browser-dot.red{background:#ff5f57}
  .browser-dot.yellow{background:#febc2e}
  .browser-dot.green{background:#28c840}
  .browser-url{flex:1;background:var(--bg);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:6px;padding:5px 12px;font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:11px;color:var(--text2);white-space:nowrap;overflow:hidden;text-overflow:ellipsis;min-width:0}
  .browser-visit{font-size:11px;font-family:var(--font-sans);font-weight:600;color:var(--text);background:var(--bg3);padding:5px 12px;border-radius:6px;flex-shrink:0;transition:opacity var(--transition)}
  .browser-visit:hover{opacity:.75}
  .browser-tabs{display:flex;gap:0;background:var(--bg2);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);overflow-x:auto;scrollbar-width:none}
  .browser-tabs::-webkit-scrollbar{display:none}
  .browser-tab{appearance:none;background:transparent;border:0;border-bottom:2px solid transparent;color:var(--text3);font-size:12px;font-family:var(--font-sans);font-weight:500;padding:10px 16px;cursor:pointer;transition:color var(--transition),border-color var(--transition);white-space:nowrap}
  .browser-tab:hover{color:var(--text2)}
  .browser-tab.active{color:var(--text);border-bottom-color:var(--text);font-weight:600}
  .browser-viewport{position:relative;width:100%;height:480px;overflow:hidden;background:var(--bg2)}
  .browser-shot{position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:auto;display:block;opacity:0;transition:opacity 220ms ease;pointer-events:none}
  .browser-shot.active{opacity:1;pointer-events:auto}
  @media (max-width:640px){
    .browser-viewport{height:360px}
    .browser-url{font-size:10px}
    .browser-visit{font-size:10px;padding:4px 10px}
    .browser-tab{padding:8px 12px;font-size:11px}
  }
</style>

<script is:inline>
  document.querySelectorAll('[data-browser]').forEach((mockup) => {
    const urlEl = mockup.querySelector('[data-browser-url]');
    const tabs = mockup.querySelectorAll('.browser-tab');
    const shots = mockup.querySelectorAll('.browser-shot');
    tabs.forEach((tab) => {
      tab.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const target = tab.dataset.tab;
        tabs.forEach((t) => {
          const on = t === tab;
          t.classList.toggle('active', on);
          t.setAttribute('aria-selected', on ? 'true' : 'false');
        });
        shots.forEach((s) => s.classList.toggle('active', s.dataset.tab === target));
        if (urlEl && tab.dataset.url) urlEl.textContent = tab.dataset.url;
      });
    });
  });
</script>
